 Maclear - A 32-year-old woman is expected in court on Monday after she was arrested on Friday afternoon by members of the Maclear Crime Prevention Unit in possession of 65kg of dagga. "The arrest follows after the members followed up on positive information received which led them to a house in the New Rest Locality area," said police spokesperson, Captain Ursula Roelofse. "The house was searched and blue plastic bags containing dagga was found. "The dagga weighed 65kg and have a street value of R65 000-00." Captain Roelofse said that the 32-year-old suspect was arrested for dealing in dagga and will appear in court on Monday. The Cluster Commander, Colonel Matshediso Gezani, commended the members on the large amount of dagga confiscated and the arrest made. “Keep up with the good work! We also want to thank the community for providing the positive information and for not tolerating this conduct in their locality”. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One.  